.TH "tipc_msg_build" 9 "tipc_msg_build" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tipc_msg_build \- create buffer chain containing specified header and data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tipc_msg_build
.BI "(struct tipc_msg *mhdr "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *m "  ","
.BI "int offset "  ","
.BI "int dsz "  ","
.BI "int pktmax "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff_head *list "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mhdr" 12
Message header, to be prepended to data
.IP "m" 12
User message
.IP "offset" 12
buffer offset for fragmented messages (FIXME)
.IP "dsz" 12
Total length of user data
.IP "pktmax" 12
Max packet size that can be used
.IP "list" 12
Buffer or chain of buffers to be returned to caller
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that the recursive call we are making here is safe, since it can
logically go only one further level down.
.SH "RETURN"
message data size or errno: -ENOMEM, -EFAULT
